# Root model in a two-hop apply chain. `parent` references `mid`, which
# in turn applies a design (`cycle`) that retargets the leaf's `x` so
# it depends on `y`. Combined with the leaf's existing `y = 2 * x`,
# this introduces a parameter cycle — surfaced by the post-build SCC
# pass as a `ParameterCycle` validation diagnostic on each member.
#
# The chain provenance lets the runtime fan out the failure against
# every file on the chain when `eval_model(parent.on)` runs:
#
# - `mid.on`: generic "applied design produced invalid contributions"
#   diagnostic at the `apply cycle to l` span.
#
# `parent.on` itself is silent because the apply lives one hop deeper.

submodel mid as m
